quran[6]{c,v,t}:
  14,22,"Once the matter has been decided, Satan will say: \"In fact, the promises which Allah made to you were all true; I too made some promises to you but failed to keep any of them. However, I had no power over you. I just invited you, and you accepted my invitation. Now! Do not blame me, but blame yourselves. I cannot help you, nor you can help me. I reject what you did before, that you associated me with Allah. Certainly such wrongdoers will have painful punishment"
  14,23,"Those who believe and do good deeds will be admitted to Paradise, beneath which rivers flow, to live therein forever with the permission of their Lord, and their greetings therein will be: \"Peace"
  14,24,"Do you not see how Allah gave the example of comparing a good word with a good tree, whose roots are firm and its branches are in the sky"
  14,25,It yields its fruits in every season by Allah’s leave. Allah cites these examples for men so that they may learn a lesson from them
  14,26,But the example of an evil word is that of an evil tree which is torn out from the earth and has no stability
  14,27,"With firm words, Allah makes the believers steadfast in the life of this world and in the hereafter; but Allah lets the wrongdoers go astray. Allah does what He pleases"